<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="416" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 702.6211/228.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Governor <persName type="from">Lister</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Olympia, Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Charges against German Consul and his Secretary filed in superior court,
                            King County, in which county Seattle is located, have been dismissed by
                            the prosecuting attorney of that county. This clears up the entire
                            situation in relation to Seattle matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ernest Lister</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>